				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote2-14445_002_006"><a name="2-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote2-14445_002_006">2.</a></span>
					<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/8.1-3?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Lucas 8:1&ndash;3</a>; cursiva agregada.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote3-14445_002_006"><a name="3-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote3-14445_002_006">3.</a></span>
					<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/24.22-23?lang=spa#21" target="_blank">Lucas 24:22&ndash;23</a>; cursiva agregada.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote4-14445_002_006"><a name="4-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote4-14445_002_006">4.</a></span>
					<p class="">En la versi&oacute;n del rey Santiago de la Biblia en ingl&eacute;s, en estos relatos aparece la frase &ldquo;certain women&rdquo; [ciertas mujeres], en que la palabra <span class="emphasis">certain</span> generalmente tiene el significado de &ldquo;una selecci&oacute;n de&rdquo; o &ldquo;una variedad de&rdquo;; sin embargo, en mi discurso del d&iacute;a de hoy deseo hacer hincapi&eacute; en otra acepci&oacute;n de esa palabra en ingl&eacute;s, que indica un sentido de seguridad, confianza y fidelidad.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote5-14445_002_006"><a name="5-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote5-14445_002_006">5.</a></span>
					<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/4.29?lang=spa#28" target="_blank">Juan 4:29</a>.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote6-14445_002_006"><a name="6-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote6-14445_002_006">6.</a></span>
					<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/4.39?lang=spa#38" target="_blank">Juan 4:39</a>.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote7-14445_002_006"><a name="7-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote7-14445_002_006">7.</a></span>
					<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/11.21-22,27?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">Juan 11:21&ndash;22, 27</a>; cursiva agregada.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote8-14445_002_006"><a name="8-14445_002_006">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote8-14445_002_006">8.</a></span>
					<p class="">V&eacute;ase Jennifer Reeder and Kate Holbrook, eds., <span class="emphasis">At the Pulpit: 185 Years of Discourses by Latter-day Saint Women</span>, 2017, p&aacute;gs. 51&ndash;52.</p>
